  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/007425.html"><b>Extrapolating
    Data From Messages</b></a><br>
    <font color="#FF0000"><i>[Quote from original post: He has also stated in
    the past, however that other issues (i.e. Class issues *cough*Ranger
    defense*cough*) can not be validated because only a minority of the people
    post here. Those issues can not be assumed to have validity because we are a
    vocal minority and dont represent the populace.]</i><br>
    </font><br>
    Theres nothing contradictory here. The twig issue has nothing to do with
    representation of popular opinion in regards to a class-complaint.
    Representation of popular opinion is a percentage-based argument, whereas representation
    of a number is a numeric argument.<br>
    <br>
    I consider the *number* of people protesting the low-delay weapons change to
    be indicative of there being a *number* of them in game.<br>
    <br>
    I consider the *number* of people protesting the current status of any class
    to be indicative of the *number* of people in game that have issues.<br>
    <br>
    I do not consider the *percentage* of people protesting the current status
    of any class to be indicative of the *percentage* of people in game that
    have issues. In other words, if 90% of [insert class] are complaining here
    on the boards, I do not believe that means that 90% of [that class] are
    unhappy.<br>
    <br>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/007394.html"><b>Bard
    Chains</b></a><br>
    <font color="#FF0000"><i>[Quote from original post: Prior to your patch of
    the level 54 AE Snare song, the lower level Chains song (level 23), for high
    level Bards, was able to stop a SINGLE damaged MOB dead in its tracks at 50%
    health. In order to do this, considering the high resist rate and the early
    break problem, Bards had to devote ALL of their casting to doing this one
    thing and this one thing alone.<br>
    <br>
    We know that green MOBs that run run at 50% health, and that blue MOBs that
    run run at 25%. After the change, the song does not stop MOBs dead in their
    tracks until 20%. This means that, prior to the level 54 patch, Bards could
    stop ALL runners. Post the level 54 patch, Bards can stop NO runners. We
    CANT STOP TRAINS now. ]</i><br>
    </font><br>
    The change that was implemented about two months ago placed a cap on the
    maximum amount that a creature can be slowed prior to the addition of
    damage. At the time, the people making that change didnt think that it would
    affect any other spells or songs than the 54th level song. After it did, and
    due to the complaints here, we tested the song in depth, and determined that
    the way it was working before was far too powerful. The current
    functionality that you are describing is the correct functionality for the
    spell.</li>
</ul>
