  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/007052.html"><b>Tracking</b></a><br>
    <font color="#FF0000"><i>[Quote from original post: In my experience,
    tracking players from short distances has never been much of a problem.
    However, tacking players that are half way across the zone is when the
    trouble begins. Heres why: I think the server only sends players information
    about other players locations on some time interval that I am really not
    sure of.]</i><br>
    </font><br>
    That would be correct. The problem that you are mentioning has to do with
    the fact that NPCs are far more predictable than players, and data outside a
    radius around the player is based off of prediction. Data within the radius
    is updated more often, but that outside gets old.<br>
    <br>
    <font color="#FF0000"><i>[Quote from original post: Purposed solution: Send
    *group* member’s location information more often. Simple as that! I
    can’t see there being much of a performance hit from that. And it will
    completely fix player tracking (if my logic is right)]</i><br>
    </font><br>
    That would dramatically increase the amount of bandwidth used. It wouldnt be
    only for those who are tracking, but for everyone.<br>
