    back out to avoid the wipe? This guy is my mule for cryin out loud : )]</i><br>
    </font><br>
    All of the information you need is at the top of the patch message. You can
    open EQNEWS.TXT in your EverQuest directory as well if you wish. However, to
    answer your question, you just need to log in, do something that will
    require your character be saved (move, trade, kill something, etc), and camp
    normally.<br>
