    <br>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/007036.html"><b>More
    Q&amp;A</b></a><br>
    <font color="#FF0000"><i>[Quote from original post: 1. Would it be possible
    (however great an idea this is) that the Quiver would fit in the Ammo Slot?
    Just seems to make sense.]</i><br>
    </font><br>
    Yes, it would make sense, but unfortunately isnt possible due to the way
    inventory works.<br>
    <br>
    <font color="#FF0000"><i>[Quote from original post: 2. Could this be a
    possible solution to your never ending Rallos Zek Coin/Item loot question (I
    know you dislike me for bringing this up but I think its a good idea if its
    feasible). Create a command similar to the /movelog &quot;yes/no&quot;
    command only make it /coinloot &quot;yes/no&quot;. ]</i><br>
    </font><br>
    We do plan to implement some kind of server-specific polling mechanism,
    however it is not likley to result in a looting change for Rallos. Though
    coin-only people might be in the majority there, there are enough people who
    want item loot across the servers that their wishes should be addressed as
    well. Item loot makes more sense on Rallos due to the reduced level-range
    for the purpose of PvP.<br>
    <br>
    The fact also remains that people who chose to play on Rallos did so knowing
    the item looting rules, and its been basically the same since release.<br>
    <br>
    <font color="#FF0000"><i>[Quote from original post: 3. This one is more of a
    logic question. Why cant rogues track? Being assassins and all, youd think
    theyd be able to pick up the trail of any target theyre after. Right? Just a
